RACE.RACE_TEXT: GULFSTREAM PARK RACE 1 6F Dirt CR: 69. Maiden Claiming Purse 19000. FOR MAIDENS, FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 119 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Claiming Price $12,500.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: MOON ROSE tracked in the two path, was driven through an opening along the rail and took the lead passing the quarter, tipped out to the two path into the stretch, and stayed on to hold off an outer rival. LAVEAU brushed with an inner foe a the start, chased from out in the seven path into the turn, ranged up in the six path rounding the turn, bid from the five path into the lane, and ran on but could not get by the inner eventual winner to place. SHARP PIPPA laid off the pace in the four path, tipped out around the turn and was ridden from the seven path into the stretch, and kept on for show. MISS UNCONCERNED hit the outer side of the gate then brushed with an outer foe at the start, stalked out in the seven path, bid from the five path passing the quarter, but flattened. UNCAPTURED SKEET set the pace in the four path, was roused in the three path midway around the turn, but lost the lead between foes nearing the quarter, had to steady at the three sixteenths, and faded. FOR THE THRILL broke out at the start, prompted the pace in the six path, was in the four path rounding the turn, but gaveway into the lane. SECRET TO SUCCESS was wellback in the three path early and never a menace.
